WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.840
On the other side of the world,

00:00:03.840 --> 00:00:07.000
Te Waka Huia and Te Whanau a Apanui

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.920
are proudly representing
Maori in haka.

00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:13.920
Our reporter Oriini Tipene-Leach

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:19.160
has left Glasgow for Edinburgh
to file this special report.

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:22.200
That's right,

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:25.320
I am outside Edinburgh Castle.

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:33.560
They've just finished rehearsals
for the Royal Military Tattoo,

00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:36.960
which is now in its 65th year.

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:42.720
Te Matatini champions.

00:00:51.080 --> 00:00:53.040
NZ's representatives

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:57.000
at one of Scotland's
biggest musical events.

00:01:25.520 --> 00:01:30.800
More than 1000 people
from around the Commonwealth

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:32.440
will take part.

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:04.920
A popular event to come back to.

00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:19.880
But tomorrow is the big day.

00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:24.600
It's the opening day for the event
which will run for three weeks.

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:27.480
Our Governor-General
Sir Jerry Mateparae

00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:30.600
and High Commissioner to UK
Sir Lockwood Smith

00:02:30.600 --> 00:02:32.680
will be there in attendance.

00:02:32.680 --> 00:02:39.440
I'll bring that story to all
of you back home on Monday, Scotty.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:42.920
That was Oriini Tipene-Leach
in Scotland.

